 hold up for any Address Verification</content><link rel='edit' type='application/atom+xml' href='http://www.blogger.com/feeds/8752543/109900201050670221/comments/default/4681093725210432717'/><link rel='self' type='application/atom+xml' href='http://www.blogger.com/feeds/8752543/109900201050670221/comments/default/4681093725210432717'/><link rel='alternate' type='text/html' href='http://guide2homelessness.blogspot.com/2004/10/employment.html?showComment=1265698710809#c4681093725210432717' title=''/><author><name>Anonymous</name><email>noreply@blogger.com</email><gd:image rel='http://schemas.google.com/g/2005#thumbnail' width='16' height='16' src='http://img1.blogblog.com/img/blank.gif'/></author><thr:in-reply-to xmlns:thr='http://purl.org/syndication/thread/1.0' href='http://guide2homelessness.blogspot.com/2004/10/employment.html' ref='tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-8752543.post-109900201050670221' source='http://www.blogger.com/feeds/8752543/posts/default/109900201050670221' type='text/html'/><gd:extendedProperty name="blogger.itemClass" value="pid-1353763913"/><gd:extendedProperty name="blogger.displayTime" value="10:58 PM"/></entry><entry><id>tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-8752543.post-1674197666981220585</id><published>2010-01-14T15:56:58.266-08:00</published><updated>2010-01-14T15:56:58.266-08:00</updated><title type='text'>First of all, great great blog. I am going to beco...</title><content type='html'>First of all, great great blog. I am going to become homeless this summer and it&amp;#39;s been extremely helpful. But about using PMBs as your home address on a job application: Wouldn&amp;#39;t the employer find out that it&amp;#39;s a private mailbox and not an actual residence when they do a background check? From what I understand being caught lying on a job application is really not good.</content><link rel='edit' type='application/atom+xml' href='http://www.blogger.com/feeds/8752543/109900201050670221/comments/default/1674197666981220585'/><link rel='self' type='